Most Kenyans don’t understand why they vote or the responsibilities of their leaders.A seminal responsibility of political parties is grooming leaders. How on earth did voters in Nairobi and Kiambu wake up early in the morning and stand in the long queues to vote in clowns? What were they thinking?
And if the two were to contest in 2022, would these voters would vote differently? I doubt it.
Mike Sonko and Ferdinand Waititu were impeached as governor of Nairobi and Kiambu County, respectively, yet they received the highest and second-highest votes, in that order, in the 2017 elections compared to their fellow country bosses.



