In their book, Responsible Parties: Saving Democracy from Itself, Frances Rosenbluth and Ian Shapiro argue that the crisis of liberal democracy today, where voters are increasingly electing populist and illiberal leaders, can be explained by the fact that we have weak, small and irresponsible political parties.
Are our political parties the the problem? Do we need strong and bigger parties? Do we even have political parties in the first place? I doubt.



